questions.question: Given that: $$ I = \int_3^4 \int_2^3 e^{(x+y)} \times dx \times dy $$. Find the value of Integration of Y with Double Integration Simpson's (3/8) Rule.

Given that: $$ I = \int_2^3 \int_2^3 e^{(x+y)} \times dx \times dy $$ x1 = 2, x2 = 3, y1 = 2, y2 = 3, number of divisions in x direction is n = 2 and number of divisions in y direction is m = 2. Find the value of h<sub>x</sub> and h<sub>y</sub> used Double Integration Simpson's (3/8) Rule.
